The paper deals with a machine learning problem (multi-instance learning) and proposes a novel framework for addressing distribution change. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions image classification (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as potential applications of their proposed framework, indicating that these sub-categories are also relevant. Finally, the paper uses causal inference techniques, which are often used in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
